{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d2a7707-7431-4bc8-b4ae-39f17ce439ce","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible project file:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — no `<PackageReference>` items needed. The SDK brings in MSTest, the runner, and CodeCoverage automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<!-- my.runsettings -->\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = one worker per core -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- parallelize across methods -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nWire it up in the csproj (inside `<PropertyGroup>`):\n\n```xml\n<TestRunSettingsFile>my.runsettings</TestRunSettingsFile>\n```\n\n**3. Run database tests sequentially** — use `[DoNotParallelize]` on those test classes:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]                    // runs sequentially, after all parallel tests\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Read_Record() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Parallelism on | `<Parallelize>` in `.runsettings` |\n| Per-core scaling | `<Workers>0</Workers>` |\n| Finest granularity | `Scope = MethodLevel` |\n| Opt-out for DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n\n`[DoNotParallelize]` classes run **after** all parallelized tests finish, so they won't conflict with anything. You can also apply it at the **method** level if only specific tests in a class need isolation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"40a42f5c-fb36-4d1d-ae06-f35790e90b7e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository appears to be empty. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk.","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"EBEB:4D1EE:7F0426:870E91:6A044F09"},"id":"322c02c3-0280-4ca4-b345-da2cd3ec336d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:14:49.340Z","parentId":"63a3c36b-6a4a-4068-843c-20aa91a77656"}
